<ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">WorldCom</ENAMEX> says it agreed to pay <ENAMEX TYPE="MONEY">$ 88 million</ENAMEX> to settle a class - action lawsuit claim that it overcharged customers on long distance telephone calls .
The settlement follows a <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">1998</ENAMEX> suit arguing that <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">WorldCom</ENAMEX> then known as <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">MCI WorldCom</ENAMEX> automatically shifted customers who were late in paying their bills into a higher rate plan .
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">MCI</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">Worldcom</ENAMEX> merged in 1998 , before splitting again <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">last year</ENAMEX> .
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">WorldCom</ENAMEX> did not admit any wrongdoing in settling the case .
